'''Burnaby''' was a federal [[electoral district (Canada)|electoral district]] in [[British Columbia]], Canada,  that was represented in the [[House of Commons of Canada]] from 1979 to 1988.

This [[Riding (division)|riding]] was created in 1976 from parts of [[Burnaby—Richmond—Delta]], [[Burnaby—Seymour]] and [[New Westminster (federal electoral district)|New Westminster]] ridings

It was abolished in 1987 when it was redistributed into [[Burnaby—Kingsway]] and [[New Westminster—Burnaby]] ridings.

